  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">REPAM: Strengthening communications for social transformation, advocacy and pastoral work.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to strengthen communications initiatives of the Pan-Amazon Ecclesial Network (REPAM), prioritising the definition, identification and practice of communication stemming directly from the Amazonian experiences, as expressed by the communities themselves. 

The project differentiates between two levels of participation. The first one, internal, is located at the community level, and fosters communication that can accompany cultural, political and spiritual processes related to the recovery of past memories, construction of new narratives, and an intercultural and intergenerational dialogue. This will strengthen the commitment to the type of communication that goes beyond the focus on delivering information alone, but can serve as a transformative tool for the people to communicate in their own manner. This internal level includes initiatives carried out by countries and local committees, as well as an adequate coordination among different actors. It will allow to broaden perspectives, accompany new initiatives and to implement a new communications service. In order to achieve this, this project will include training and coordination with a national, regional and international perspective.

The second, external, level refers to communications work related to Laudato Si and Integral Ecology and includes an international campaign and advocacy.  

This project is a direct continuation of the previous one, which was initially set up to support the creation of the REPAM itself. As the network grew and became established, the previous project started focusing on the communications work of the network, which the partner decided to carry over into this new project.</narrative>
  </description>
